By Ekemini Ladejobi Charles Oputa, popularly known as Charly Boy, says his 40-year-old marriage to Diane has not been easy and `still dey leak’ (having challenges). Charly Boy, who took to his instagram to give an insight into his marriage, said that every marriage has its issues. The veteran musician and activist said he and his wife have agreed never to give up on each other. Charly Boy said further that “marriage is management” and not “everyone will get married”. Below are some of the extracts: “Some people think say marriage na moimoi. How dem fit know say no be everybody God create go marry. “I don swim many rivers for dis my 40-sometin years marriage.  “Don’t for one minute think our marriage is made in heaven. It has been through Hell many times over, we still dey patch am, e still dey leak. “We have our issues, problems and challenges (never for public consumption). We disagree on many things smtimes. “The ONLY Thing we basically Agree on, is never to give up on each other. “We both go die here I think. Biko enjoy ur weekend for marriage is management. “May God bless your Union, too.’’ (NAN)  Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related 54-year-old mother of 15 children shares ordealMrs Hussaina Salisu, 54-year-old woman, with 15 children has advised young mothers to plan their families for better future .November 10, 2020In "General News"Court dissolves 11-year-old marriage over battery, threat to lifeA Mapo Customary Court in Ibadan has dissolved the marriage between two school teachers, John Fawole and his wife, Mary, over bthreat to lifeSeptember 25, 2020In "Judiciary"Court refuses to dissolve 10-year-old marriage The Ka